				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Does anyone know anything about this? Taken from eqlive:
<br />

<br />
Upcoming for August 2004
<br />
We have an update tentatively scheduled for early August.  You can look forward to seeing;
<br />

<br />
PVP Changes for the PVP servers.  
<br />

<br />
And many other exciting changes.  Stay tuned.
<br />

<br />
Brenlo the Updated
<br />

<br />

<br />
People on my server have been yelling and screaming that this was supposed to happen last night.  Supposedly, the only non-pvp zone will be bazaar...someone tell me why that isnt the worst idea I have heard.  As if the bazaar wasnt laggy enough.  How are your supposed to zone into pok?  I also heard that the loot system was changing so you would get points instead of being able to loot items?  Wont pk's just take advantage by pk'ing eachother?  Half of them are de-lvld anyway, so how does the new changes make pvp more fair? 
<br />

<br />
Anyone have any updates or any thoughts on this?<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=768652" target="_blank" class="postlink">Dunador</a>
